-- Hilton, Inveravante Group to Open Hotels in Morocco’s Tangier
-- B y   Z a i n a b   F a t t a h
-- 2012-07-02T06:49:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/hilton-inveravante-group-to-open-hotels-in-morocco-s-tangier.html
Hilton Worldwide, a unit of
 Blackstone Group LP (BX)  in 2007, agreed with Inveravante Group to
operate two new hotels in the Moroccan city of Tangier.  The two properties, Hilton Tanger City Center Hotel &
Residences and Hilton Garden Inn Tanger City Center, are the
 operator’s  first in the city, the company said in an e-mailed
statement today.  The 182-room Hotel & Residences will include 68 apartments
and is scheduled to open in 2015. The Hilton Garden Inn will
have 233 rooms and opens in December 2014, according to the
statement.  Inveravante, founded by Manuel Jove Capellan in 2007, has
energy and food businesses as well as real estate and tourism,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
